data.content:
adjective
always used before a noun
chiefly US :having a high position or the highest position in a group or organization
a ranking news analyst
Who is the ranking officer here?
the country's ranking law school - see also high-ranking, low-ranking, top-ranking
noun
plural -ings
rankings [plural] :a list of people or things that are ordered according to their quality, ability, size, etc.
She is currently fifth in the world gymnastics rankings. [=she is ranked as the fifth best gymnast in the world]
He is number two in the class rankings.
[count] :the position of a person or thing in the rankings
The new coach led the team to a No. 1 ranking.
